1. Ja sam pogodio *meta* iz prve (I hit the *target* on my first try)
2. Nadam se da ćeš uskoro pogoditi *pravu* odluku (I hope you'll make the *right* decision soon)
3. Ako pogodiš *brojeve*, osvojićeš nagradu (If you guess the *numbers*, you'll win a prize)
4. Ona je bila pogodna za *posao* (She was suitable for the *job*)
5. Mogao sam da pogodim iz koje *zemlje* dolaze (I could guess where they come from)
6. Jelena je pokušala da pogodi koliko ima *novca* u kasi (Jelena tried to guess how much *money* was in the cash register)
7. Ne mogu da pogodim ko je pobedio na takmičenju (I can't guess who won the competition)
8. Pogodio me je talas emocija kada sam čuo tu pesmu (I was hit by a wave of emotions when I heard that song)
9. Pogodila me je spoznaja da nisam u pravu (The realization that I was wrong hit me)
10. Da li si pogodio šta mi je danas na pameti? (Did you guess what's on my mind today?)

Note: In Serbian language, the verb "pogoditi" can have several meanings depending on the context. It can mean "to hit", "to guess", "to suit", "to match", "to realize", etc.